snippet: The number of new applications for unemployment benefits have now kept below a threshold that signals a strong job market for 33 weeks.
abstract: National Assn of Realtors says home resales rose 4.7 percent in September, to annual rate of 5.55 million units; Labor Dept reports initial claims for state unemployment insurance rose 3,000 to seasonally adjusted 259,000 in latest week.
lead_paragraph: The number of new applications for unemployment benefits have now kept below a threshold that signals a strong job market for 33 weeks.

headline.print_headline: Upbeat News in Jobs Data and Rate of Home Resales
